below are the commands to run in the Arch-Linux installer.
the commented commands must be executed ONLY in case you don't have more partitions on your ssd!!!

"installation with ArchLinux Vanilla"
##mkfs.vfat -F32 /dev/<partition EFI>
##mkswap /dev/<partition swap>
mkfs.btrfs /dev/<partition main>
mount /dev/<partition main> /mnt
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@home
umount -R /mnt
mount -o subvol=@ /dev/<partition main> /mnt
mkdir -p /mnt/home
mount -o subvol=@home /dev/<partition main> /mnt/home
mount
##mkdir -p /mnt/boot/efi
##mount /dev/<partition EFI> /mnt/boot/efi
##swapon /dev/<partition swap>

"installation of an ArchLinux-based distro"
packages to install to make timeshift snapshots load on grub:
sudo pacman -S btrfs-progs grub-btrfs

Snapshot management:
yay -S cronie timeshift-bin timeshift-autosnap
sudo systemctl enable cronie
sudo systemctl start cronie

small script that allows us to upload all snapshots generated by timeshift to grub (in my case every 2 hours) with cronie
Script GRUB:
nano <namefile.sh>
sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
chmod 777 <namefile.sh>

CRON JOB:
sudo EDITOR=nano crontab -e
0 */2 * * * <namefile.sh> ---> every two hours every day
sudo crontab -l

